<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Lo-Fi Python - coding, programming, text editors</title><link>https://lofipython.com/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 07 Aug 2023 13:56:00 -0500</lastBuildDate><item><title>Opening Files From The Terminal With Text Editor CLIs</title><link>https://lofipython.com/opening-files-in-the-shell-or-terminal-with-text-editor-clis.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Many text editors have the ability to open files from a computer's shell. Here are a few text editor commands that I've learned for opening a file automatically from the command line:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sublime&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;subl file.txt&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;VS Code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;code file.py&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emacs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class="code console literal-block"&gt;
&lt;span class="go"&gt;emacs -nw file.txt&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
